HEADWORD: Odyssey
<hw>Od"ys*sey</hw> <pr>(⟦ocr⟧d"⟦icr⟧s*s⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Odyssea</ets>, Gr. <grk>'Ody`sseia</grk>, fr.
<grk>'Odyssey`s</grk> Ulysses: cf. F. <ets>Odyss⟦eacute⟧e</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An epic poem attributed to <persfn>Homer</persfn>, which describes
the return of <persfn>Ulysses</persfn> to <city>Ithaca</city> after the
siege of <city>Troy</city>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

